snippet.textDisplay: I'm being completely honest here...anyone watching the game (and yes I saw it) would wonder what could've happened had Morelos not dived 4 times.  Now I know some will be thinking as a celtic fan I'm making it up or out to get Morelos but I'm not one of those types.  Honestly if you see the replays Morelos went down 4 times (I counted) ...watch the replays.. he had the ball and went down when no one touched him.  He threw himself down another 3 times.  He was booked once but on the last one he did feel a hand on his shoulder but again there was no force, in front of the ref, and it was minimal, but Morelos totally just made a BAD dying swan impression and went down like a skydiver hitting the floor.  Had Morelos stayed on his feet and kept control of the ball during those dives he might have got a snap shot on goal and actually scored.   Needless to say the rest of Rangers didn't play great either and some credit has to go to Kilmarnock as they did have you penned back for a bit.  Rangers only started seeing more of the ball after Kilmarnock scored and sat back to protect the draw.  Like I said I'm just basing things on what I saw.  The season isn't done but it does mean you are relying on Rangers winning every game and Celtic loosing about 3 in the next 13.  I don't see it happening.  I don't think Gerrard can be blamed for players under performing.  You've still got Europe and a cup to play for, but I personally recon the league is over. I also recon the 4th Treble is on it's way to Celtic in 2020.   Its been interesting guys... see you next season.

I just feel deflated. It feels the exact same as last year. Same stupid mistakes and not learning from them and changing things up. Gerrard needs to understand when subs are needed, he’s still waiting too long to make the subs when it’s obvious a change is needed 20 minutes beforehand.
Even though I understand why they had their hands up to say “ref that was a handball, goal shouldn’t have counted” - nah fuck that play to the whistle and when it goes out for a goal kick or throw in then you complain, too many times we stop playing to argue a decision when the other team keeps playing and scores from it.
6 months of hard work and grinding out results and even getting out of the group in Europe and beating them at their ground for the first time in nearly 10 years... all means virtually nothing now that we’ve messed up in January and February.

We can’t blame the refs when the team isn’t doing enough to look like they even want to win games. That’s 3 times now since we’ve came back from the winter break that we’ve been desperate for a goal in the last minutes of a game and instead of throwing everyone and everything at it, everyone running their arses off to get chances and get a goal, we pass it back and sidewards in the midfield and defence in an attempt to walk the ball into the net even though it hasn’t worked all game and the opposition has everyone behind the ball to defend a draw or a lead.

Like it or not, the Taig Vermin have significantly more money, slightly better players & a stronger squad. Realistically, around 75 points pre-split was the best that could be hoped for. If the Forces of Darkness got more than that, there wasn't a realistic hope of matching them. The Spoonburners, Jambos & Killie have all been in various degrees of disarray since May, while even the Sheep have stuttered.
